and literary people tend to write

00:13:58.490 --> 00:14:00.610
about what's going backward?

00:14:00.610 --> 00:14:02.480
&gt;&gt; James Gleick: Well,
that's interesting.

00:14:02.480 --> 00:14:07.500 position:56%
I mean, maybe we should-- let's have
a-- can we have a show of hands?

00:14:07.500 --> 00:14:09.040
Here's a question.

00:14:09.040 --> 00:14:15.000
You've got a time machine, you
